observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) to strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of infrastructure projects;

Municipal Engineer to strictly monitor the implementation of the contract to ensure compliance with Annex E of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184, and ensure compliance of the contractor with the full disclosure policy by accomplishing the required information in the signboard/ tarpaulin as an integral part of supporting documents for claim of payment;

Municipal Accountant to submit the complete and duly authenticated supporting documents prescribed under Section 9.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001; and

BAC/GSO to observe the timely submission of advance copies of contracts within five (5) working days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) to strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of goods particularly, Annex H Consolidated Guidelines for the Alternative Methods of Procurement;

Supplier to post the performance security and warranty security to fully protect the interest of the Municipality in case of manufacturing defects and failures;

Municipal Accountant to review the regularity and completeness of supporting documents prescribed under Section 9.2.5 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 before processing claims for payment;

General Services Officer (GSO) and/or office/department, responsible for accepting deliveries, to: (i) notify the Audit Team within 24 hours from acceptance of all deliveries of goods, and inform the Audit Team of the time and date of the scheduled deliveries to avoid delay or failure in the conduct of inspection and other audit procedures necessary in accordance with COA Circular No. 95-006; and (ii) prepare the Property Acknowledgement Receipt duly received by the person directly responsible for the safekeeping of multi-cabs indicating the description and the unit cost, among others to facilitate verification; and

BAC/GSO to observe the timely submission of advance copies of contracts within five (5) working days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001.

