BAC/GSO to observe the timely submission of advance copies of contracts within five (5) working days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the:

Municipal Treasurer to take possible steps/strategies and exert more efforts to collect the loan receivable accounts from borrowers to ensure cash availability for future beneficiaries of various loan programs; Encourage the borrowers to pay their obligation on time, otherwise they will be blacklisted and could no longer avail of other livelihood assistance from the Municipality and other livelihood loans that may be extended by other national government agencies in the future;

Municipal Accountant to conduct regular and periodic verification of loan receivable accounts to determine its conditions that would affect its collectability. Also, update and ensure that the aging schedule is reconciled with the amounts in the statement of financial position.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

Bids and Awards Committee to strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of Infrastructure Projects;

Municipal Engineer to strictly monitor the implementation of projects to ensure compliance with Annexes E of RA No. 9184 and ensure compliance with the full disclosure policy by taking photographs of signboard as an integral part of supporting documents for claim of payment; 

Municipal Accountant to submit the complete and duly authenticated supporting documents prescribed under Section 9.1 of COA Circular No. 2012 – 001; and 

BAC/GSO to observe the timely submission of advance copies of contracts within five (5) working days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

Bids and Awards Committee to (i) strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of goods particularly, Annex H, Consolidated Guidelines for the Alternative Method of Procurement; (ii) consider procuring common-used goods, supplies from the DBM-PS; and (iii) subject procurement as far as practicable to public bidding unless the conditions are present for the use of shopping or small value procurement as alternative mode of procurement;

Municipal Accountant to submit the complete and duly authenticated supporting documents prescribed under Sections 9.1 and 9.1.3 of COA Circular No. 2012 - 001 and for future transactions, ensure that the supporting documents are complete before processing for payments.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the:
Municipal Treasurer to take possible steps/strategies and exert more efforts to collect the loan receivable accounts from borrowers to ensure cash availability for future beneficiaries of various loan programs; Encourage the borrowers to pay their obligation on time, otherwise they will be blacklisted and could no longer avail of other livelihood assistance from the Municipality and other livelihood loans that may be extended by other national government agencies in the future;
Municipal Accountant to conduct regular and periodic verification of loan receivable accounts to determine its conditions that would affect its collectability. Also, update and ensure that the aging schedule is reconciled with the amounts in the statement of financial position.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
Bids and Awards Committee to strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of Infrastructure Projects;
Municipal Engineer to strictly monitor the implementation of projects to ensure compliance with Annexes E of RA No. 9184 and ensure compliance with the full disclosure policy by taking photographs of signboard as an integral part of supporting documents for claim of payment;
Municipal Accountant to submit the complete and duly authenticated supporting documents prescribed under Section 9.1 of COA Circular No. 2012 – 001; and
BAC/GSO to observe the timely submission of advance copies of contracts within five (5) working days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
Bids and Awards Committee to (i) strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of goods particularly, Annex H, Consolidated Guidelines for the Alternative Method of Procurement; (ii) consider procuring common-used goods, supplies from the DBM-PS; and (iii) subject procurement as far as practicable to public bidding unless the conditions are present for the use of shopping or small value procurement as alternative mode of procurement;
Municipal Accountant to submit the complete and duly authenticated supporting documents prescribed under Sections 9.1 and 9.1.3 of COA Circular No. 2012 - 001 and for future transactions, ensure that the supporting documents are complete before processing for payments.

We recommended that the:

BAC strictly comply with the IRR of RA No. 9184 and the Consolidated Guidelines for the Alternative Methods of Procurement prescribed under Annex H of the Revised Implementing Rules and Regulation of RA No. 9184;

require the supplier to post performance security and warranty security in order to fully protect the interest of the Municipality in case of manufacturing defects and failures;

Municipal Accountant review the regularity and completeness of supportingdocuments prescribed under Section 9.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 before processing claims for payment; and

Municipal Mayor consider designating a regular employee to act as Supply Officer who must be properly bonded in accordance with law.

We also recommended that the BAC and the Municipal Accountant render a satisfactory explanation for the deficiencies noted in the procurement of one unit dump truck for use of MDRRMO.
